23. Actors Identification
Actors represent external entities that interact with the Cybersecurity Incident Reporting & Response System. Identifying actors helps in understanding system interactions and defining use cases.
The following actors have been identified:
Employee/ Incident Reporter
Reports suspected or confirmed cybersecurity incidents and views incident status updates.
SOC Analyst
Analyses reported incidents, performs severity assessment, follows response workflows, and updates incident status.
System Administrator / Security Manager
Manages system users, roles, configurations, monitors incident activity, and generates compliance and audit reports.
Notification System
Sends alerts and notifications to relevant stakeholders regarding incident reporting, severity changes, and status updates.
These actors interact with the system to ensure efficient reporting, timely response, and effective management of cybersecurity incidents across the organization.

